==Ancient Greek==

===Etymology===
From {{inh|grc|ine-pro|*ḱwṓ}}. Cognates include {{cog|la|canis}}, {{cog|sa|श्वन्|tr=śván}} and {{cog|ang|hund}} ({{cog|en|hound}}). The final {{m|grc||-ν}} in the nominative singular which was absent in {{m|ine-pro|*ḱwṓ}} was restored in Greek by analogy to other forms in the paradigm.

